description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Clinical Nurse Manager at the West of England Eye Unit at the Royal Devon and Exeter Foundation Trust. WEEU is responsible for providing specialist ophthalmic care across Devon. This is a fantastic opportunity to lead and develop our dynamic service and staff at our Wonford site. Ideal for an experienced nurse who is flexible, enthusiastic and passionate about caring for patients and the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work in partnership with our multidisciplinary team of Ophthalmologists, Ophthalmic nurses, Orthoptists, Optometrists, Health care assistants, Ophthalmic technicians, medical photographers, medical secretaries and receptionists to deliver safe and compassionate Ophthalmic services across our outpatient, Theatres and Daycare areas .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Clinical Nurse Managers role is to ensure the quality and safety of all patients within the division and to ensure that a high standard of clinical care is delivered by the entire multidisciplinary team at all times. Candidates will need to be passionate about ensuring that the work force you lead delivers the highest standards of care to all patients and ensuring the patient experience is positive.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; We offer a friendly supportive environment that values individuals in their personal and professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like any further information or would like to arrange an informal visit. Please contact Carly Slade, Clinical Matron of Ophthalmology via email carly.slade@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vision is to provide safe, high quality seamless services delivered with courtesy and respect. To achieve our vision we expect all our staff to uphold our Trust values. Our Trust values are: &lt;br /&gt; Honesty, Openness &amp; Integrity&lt;br /&gt; Fairness&lt;br /&gt; Inclusion &amp; Collaboration&lt;br /&gt; Respect &amp; Dignity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to staff with ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon.***&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DUE TO THE ANTICIPATED HIGH NUMBER OF APPLICATIONS FOR THIS POST WE RESERVE THE RIGHT TO CLOSE THE VACANCY BEFORE THE CLOSING DATE.&lt;/p&gt;
